articles.description: — Ryan Poehling had a goal and two assists, Joel Farabee added a goal and an assist and the Philadelphia Flyers won their fifth straight game, beating the slumping Columbus Blue Jackets 5-2 on Sunday night.

articles.description: Aleksander Barkov escaped major injury in a knee-to-knee collision and is being listed by the Panthers as day-to-day.

articles.description: — William Nylander scored at 3:09 of overtime, and the Toronto Maple Leafs extended their winning streak to four with a 4-3 victory over the Minnesota Wild on Sunday in the final game of the NHL’s Global Series in Sweden.
articles.headline: Nylander scores in OT, Maple Leafs extend win streak to 4 with 4-3 victory over Wild in Sweden

images.name: Maple Leafs win in OT with a William Nylander goal
images.caption: Morgan Rielly assists on William Nylander's overtime goal to boost the Leafs past the Wild.
